    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Lynn J. Montross (1895-1961) was a United States Marine Corps historian and specialist in military
history, best known for his <emph render="italic">War Through the Ages</emph> (1960).  He served in the American Expeditionary Forces for three years during World War I and was a freelance writer for the <emph render="italic">Chicago Daily News</emph>.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
      <p>The <emph render="bold">Lynn J. Montross Papers</emph> contains correspondence, scrapbooks, research notes, published and unpublished articles, manuscripts and other material.  The collection remains largely in original order and in the donors original file folders.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
      <head>Arrangement of the Collection</head>
      <p>The collection has received minimal processing and is largely in original order.</p>
    </arrangement>
